For $ expansion: Only search for variables that have valid variable names (alphanumeric characters and underscore, not starting with a digit).
It causes this to not work:
export A=a
export $A=b
 
Executable with no exec permissions:
Just don't check executable permissions when searching for an executable in the PATH env variable.
You will say command not found, and have exit code 127 instead of 126.
 
 
